COLORATION IN LIFE: Pinkish-brown, grey, or reddish-brown (nonbreeding, sexually quiescent individuals) to bright yellowish-orange, orangish-red, or bright red (breeding, sexually active individuals) ground coloration, with two prominent vertical and generally converging (below the lateral midline) dark gray to jet black midlateral bars (de 
Rham and Nourissat, 2004: 122
). Total of six or seven vertical bars present on flanks. Apart from two prominent midlateral bars, representing the second and third or third and fourth bars in series, remaining bars generally faint, although those on posterior region of flank easily visible. Fins gray, pinkish brown, or reddish brown and similar to base body coloration in nonbreeding individuals, and solid yellowish orange, orangish red, or bright red in breeding individuals. Lips, lower cheek, gular region, and belly very pale blue or grey in sexually active individuals (see photographs in de 
Rham and Nourissat, 2004: 122
).
